<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-05-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-05-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="475" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d475">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Dudley</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Petropolis</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-05-18"><hi rend="italic">May 18,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Reference department’s May 15. Rio Branco to-day assented to proposed
                            publication of joint note in the three capitals. Publication here,
                            though complete as a Portuguese translation, may purport to be a
                            résumé.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dudley.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>